## Authentication & Session Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as 👤 User (Browser)
    participant FE as React Frontend
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant AUTH as src/auth.py
    participant DB as data/users.csv

    U->>FE: Click Register / Login
    FE->>API: POST /register (username, password)
    API->>AUTH: get_password_hash(password)
    AUTH->>DB: Append hashed row
    DB-->>API: OK
    API-->>FE: 200 "Registered"

    U->>FE: Login credentials
    FE->>API: POST /login (OAuth2PasswordRequestForm)
    API->>AUTH: verify_password()
    AUTH->>DB: lookup username
    DB-->>AUTH: hashed_password
    AUTH-->>API: ✅ verified
    API->>AUTH: create_access_token (HS256, 7-day)
    AUTH-->>API: JWT token
    API-->>FE: {access_token, token_type}
    FE->>FE: Store token in localStorage

    Note over FE,API: Every protected request sends Bearer token
    FE->>API: POST /recommend/content + Authorization: Bearer <token>
    API->>AUTH: get_current_user(token)
    AUTH->>AUTH: jwt.decode → username
    AUTH-->>API: User object
    API-->>FE: Recommendations
```

