## TF-IDF vs BERT Embedding Detail

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph TF_IDF["TF-IDF (Lexical Matching)"]
        direction TB
        T1["Input: raw text string"]
        T2["Tokenize + remove stopwords\nngrams (1,2)"]
        T3["Vocab: 1000 most frequent terms"]
        T4["TF × IDF weight per term"]
        T5["Output: sparse vector\n1 × 1000  most dims = 0"]
        T1-->T2-->T3-->T4-->T5
    end

    subgraph BERT_SEC["Sentence-BERT (Semantic Matching)"]
        direction TB
        B1["Input: raw text string"]
        B2["WordPiece tokenizer\n(max 512 tokens)"]
        B3["12-layer Transformer\nall-MiniLM-L6-v2"]
        B4["Mean pooling over\ntoken embeddings"]
        B5["Output: dense vector\n1 × 384  all dims active"]
        B1-->B2-->B3-->B4-->B5
    end

    subgraph HYBRID_SEC["Hybrid Score Fusion"]
        direction TB
        H1["tfidf_cosine  0.15 weight\nExact keyword matching"]
        H2["bert_cosine   0.60 weight\nSemantic/contextual meaning"]
        H3["skill_cosine  0.20 weight\nPer-skill BERT similarity"]
        H4["exp_ratio     0.05 weight\nSeniority alignment"]
        H5["Σ → final_score"]
        H1 & H2 & H3 & H4 --> H5
    end

    T5 -->|cosine| H1
    B5 -->|cosine| H2
    B5 -->|per-skill cosine| H3
```

